      correctAnswer: "Gunicorn is a production WSGI server that handles multiple requests simultaneously, unlike Flask's single-threaded development server",
      explanation: "Flask's built-in server (app.run()) is single-threaded and designed only for development — it can only handle one request at a time. Gunicorn spawns multiple worker processes. Flask explicitly warns: 'Do not use the development server in a production environment.'"
