      correctAnswer: "userId as Partition Key and eventTimestamp as Sort Key",
      explanation: "DynamoDB stores all items with the same Partition Key together, sorted by Sort Key. Setting userId as Partition Key means all events for that user are co-located. The Sort Key eventTimestamp enables time-sorted queries with KeyConditionExpression."
