      options: ["Reflected XSS", "Stored XSS", "DOM-based XSS", "CSRF"],
      correctAnswer: "Stored XSS",
      explanation: "Stored XSS (also called Persistent XSS) saves the malicious script in the server's database. Every user who views the affected page executes the script. This is the most dangerous type because it does not require victims to click a crafted link."
