      correctAnswer: "nohup ./deploy.sh &",
      explanation: "The 'nohup' command ('no hangup') prevents the process from receiving the SIGHUP signal when the terminal closes. The '&' sends it to the background. Together, the script runs even after Arjun disconnects his SSH session."
