      correctAnswer: "=A2*$B$1",
      explanation: "=A2*$B$1 uses a relative reference for A2 (so it shifts to A3, A4... as you copy down) and an absolute reference for $B$1 (so it always points to the tax rate cell). This is the correct pattern for applying a fixed rate to a varying list."
