      correctAnswer: "BonusRate",
      explanation: "Once a cell is given a Named Range, you can use that name directly in formulas instead of the cell address. =C2*BonusRate is cleaner, self-documenting, and will not break if rows or columns are inserted — making it far better practice than hardcoded cell references."
