      correctAnswer: "__",
      explanation: "BEM uses __ (double underscore) to separate Block from Element: .card__button means 'the button element of the card block'. It uses -- (double hyphen) for Modifiers: .card__button--disabled means 'the disabled state of the button element inside the card block'. BEM makes CSS self-documenting — you know the component structure just from reading the class names."
