      correctAnswer: "[(1,'a'), (2,'b'), (3,'c')]",
      explanation: "zip() pairs up corresponding elements from two (or more) iterables into tuples. The result is an iterator of tuples. Wrapping with list() materializes it. This is used constantly for pairing parallel data like names+scores or keys+values."
