      explanation: "pd.read_csv() is one of the most-used functions in data analysis. It reads a CSV file and returns a DataFrame. You can also use pd.read_excel() for Excel files, pd.read_json() for JSON, and pd.read_sql() for database queries — all returning DataFrames ready for analysis."
