      correctAnswer: "plt.savefig()",
      explanation: "plt.savefig('filename.png') saves the current figure to a file. Common arguments: dpi (dots per inch — 150-300 for quality), bbox_inches='tight' (removes extra whitespace), format='pdf'/'png'/'svg'. Call it BEFORE plt.show() or plt.close()."
