      correctAnswer: "Yes — views run the underlying query fresh each time they are queried",
      explanation: "Views are virtual — they store the query definition, not data. Every time you SELECT from a view, MySQL executes the underlying query against the current data in the base tables. New rows inserted after view creation are immediately visible when querying the view."
