      options: ["One-to-One", "One-to-Many", "Many-to-Many", "Zero-to-Many"],
      correctAnswer: "Many-to-Many",
      explanation: "Many-to-Many means both sides can have multiple matching records. This requires a junction/bridge table (e.g., employee_projects with employee_id and project_id) to represent the relationship in a relational database, since a single column can't store multiple values."
